        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add alphabetical sort toggle to providers pane",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\n  - Add a sort toggle button beside the Providers search bar that orders providers alphabetically with enabled providers also sorted alphabetically on top.\r\n  - Default the pane to alphabetical sorting; persist the choice across view changes and sessions via `providersSortedAlphabetically` (UserDefaults).\r\n  - Keep sorting non-destructive — it's a display overlay computed by\r\n  `CodexBarConfig.alphabeticalProviderOrder(...)` and never rewrites the user's stored manual order.\r\n  - Hide the drag-to-reorder handles while sorting is on, and restore them (and the saved order) when it's off.\r\n  - Re-sort live as providers are enabled/disabled while the toggle is active.\r\n\r\n  ## Proof\r\n\r\n  - `swift test --filter 'SettingsStoreTests'` (61 tests passed)\r\n  - New coverage: toggle defaults off + persists across instances; `alphabeticalProviderOrder` puts enabled providers first and sorts each group case-insensitively by display name.\r\n  - `swift test --filter 'SettingsStoreCoverageTests|StatusMenuTests|ProvidersPane|PreferencesProviders'` (201 tests passed) — confirms `orderedProviders()` / menu-bar ordering is unchanged.\r\n  - `swift build` (clean)\r\n\r\n## Screen recording\r\n\r\nWith sorting _off_:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"790\" height=\"749\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-18 at 3 43 53 PM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/068d4851-7c78-450c-b023-70e8355f8671\" />\r\n\r\nWith sorting _on_:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"779\" height=\"747\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-18 at 3 42 52 PM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/8ba3c989-41d9-421c-91ac-14a061705fa7\" />\r\n\r\n",
